Infer file type

Source: R/file_types.R
pxFileTypes.Rd

The pxFileTypes() function inferres mass spectrometry and proteomics file types based on a currated table of file types and associated patterns. This table can be accessed with fileTypes(). See the examples below for the content of the tables.

The file types table is generated by scripts/make_fileTypes.R.

fileTypes()

pxFileTypes(fls, types = fileTypes())

Arguments

fls

character() of file names whose types need to be inferred based on their file extenstion.

types

data.frame of file types. Default is fileTypes().

Value

A data.frame with the filenames and their inferred types.

Author

Laurent Gatto with contributions from Dr. Samuel Wein to identify several file types.

pxFileTypes("foo")
#>   file type
#> 1  foo <NA>
pxFileTypes("foo.mzML")
#>       file type
#> 1 foo.mzML  raw
pxFileTypes("foo.raw")
#>      file   type
#> 1 foo.raw binary
pxFileTypes("foo.txt")
#>      file type
#> 1 foo.txt  doc
pxFileTypes("foo.R")
#>    file type
#> 1 foo.R code
pxFileTypes("foo.fasta")
#>        file type
#> 1 foo.fasta  fas

pxFileTypes(c("foo", "foo.mzML", "foo.R", "foo.fasta"))
#>        file type
#> 1       foo <NA>
#> 2  foo.mzML  raw
#> 3     foo.R code
#> 4 foo.fasta  fas
